gender, number of family members and age were significant for the choice of the mode of the
trips, highlighting the fact that the higher the income, the greater the preference for driving a
car to the detriment of walking or transit riding, which causes the need for studying solutions
to provide a sustainable mobility that also reaches the highest income classes.

